513
00:37:02,735 --> 00:37:05,062
It was a slight error in judgement.

514
00:37:06,335 --> 00:37:08,791
Honey, please don't give me 
the silent treatment.

515
00:37:10,735 --> 00:37:12,900
I'm not.

516
00:37:12,935 --> 00:37:14,931
Did you say you read this?

517
00:37:15,435 --> 00:37:17,186
Yeah, part of it. Why?

518
00:37:19,635 --> 00:37:24,293
Mrs Huber was blackmailing Zach's mom.

519
00:37:39,500 --> 00:37:40,300
Zach?

520
00:38:09,500 --> 00:38:10,949
What are you doing up?

521
00:38:12,435 --> 00:38:19,400
Couldn't sleep, so I was just--
sitting here. Thinking.

522
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:23,486
About what?

523
00:38:26,535 --> 00:38:29,165
Do you really want to know?

524
00:38:29,735 --> 00:38:31,209
Bree--

525
00:38:31,335 --> 00:38:36,300
I'm not feeling too hot right now.
So just tell me. What's up?

526
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:43,100
I was thinking that the biggest mistake 
of my entire life was agreeing to marry you.

527
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:51,541
Let me guess.
I've done something wrong.

528
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:56,500
Forcing me into sharing
your depraved pastime wasn't bad enough?

529
00:38:56,535 --> 00:39:00,800
You had to share my humiliation
with your co-workers?

530
00:39:00,835 --> 00:39:01,900
What?

531
00:39:01,935 --> 00:39:05,600
Rex, everybody is talking about our sex life.

532
00:39:05,635 --> 00:39:10,300
Every sordid little detail, right down to
that box of perversions you keep in the closet!

533
00:39:10,335 --> 00:39:13,400
Bree, I never said anything to anyone,
I swear to God!

534
00:39:13,435 --> 00:39:14,100
You're a liar.

535
00:39:14,135 --> 00:39:15,700
Who told you this?

536
00:39:15,735 --> 00:39:16,400
Doesn't matter.

537
00:39:16,435 --> 00:39:18,400
It does matter, because I never said anything!

538
00:39:18,435 --> 00:39:21,600
Then how do people know?
Because we both know that I wouldn't say anything!

539
00:39:21,635 --> 00:39:23,800
Why would I tell people about what we do in bed?

540
00:39:23,835 --> 00:39:26,100
[---] Maybe you were bragging.

541
00:39:26,135 --> 00:39:29,200
Or maybe you just subconsciously wanted to hurt me.

542
00:39:29,235 --> 00:39:32,500
Congratulations, you did it!
I am officially destroyed!

543
00:39:32,535 --> 00:39:36,864
I didn't say anything!
- I don't believe you.

544
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,007
Oh.

545
00:39:42,500 --> 00:39:43,500
Oh.

546
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,500
Rex?

547
00:39:46,535 --> 00:39:50,200
What? What is it?

548
00:39:50,235 --> 00:39:52,487
I think I'm having a heart attack.

549
00:39:54,935 --> 00:39:56,657
No, you're not.

550
00:39:58,135 --> 00:40:01,973
Bree, you're going to have to
take me to the hospital.

551
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:06,986
Um--

552
00:40:07,835 --> 00:40:11,100
All right, you-- go downstairs and, um,

553
00:40:11,135 --> 00:40:15,365
I will be--
I'll be right there.

554
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:33,188
Daddy?

555
00:40:34,035 --> 00:40:36,000
What are you doing?

556
00:40:36,035 --> 00:40:40,000
I'm waiting for your mother
to take me to the Emergency Room.

557
00:40:40,035 --> 00:40:44,100
What's wrong?
- I'm having a heart attack.

558
00:40:44,135 --> 00:40:46,512
Oh my God, where is she?

559
00:40:46,535 --> 00:40:47,962
That's a good question.

560
00:40:51,235 --> 00:40:53,382
Daddy says he's having a heart attack.

561
00:40:53,435 --> 00:40:57,800
I know. I'm going to 
take him to the hospital.

562
00:40:57,835 --> 00:40:58,801
Well, when?

563
00:41:01,735 --> 00:41:04,179
When I finish making the bed.

564
00:41:04,535 --> 00:41:06,185
What?

565
00:41:06,735 --> 00:41:10,500
I never leave the house with an unmade bed.
You know that.

566
00:41:10,535 --> 00:41:13,402
But Daddy needs to go the hospital.

567
00:41:15,900 --> 00:41:18,283
There. 
Now we can go.

568
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:33,100
<i>Nothing is forever.

569
00:41:33,135 --> 00:41:38,100
<i>And the time comes when we all
must say goodbye to the world we know.

570
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:46,800
<i>Goodbye to everything
we had taken for granted.

571
00:41:50,900 --> 00:41:55,900
<i>Goodbye to those
we thought would never abandon us.

572
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:05,600
<i>And when these changes finally do occur,

573
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:11,000
<i>when the familiar has departed
and the unfamiliar has taken its place,

574
00:42:14,100 --> 00:42:17,300
<i>all any of us can really do

575
00:42:17,335 --> 00:42:20,900
<i>is to say hello

576
00:42:20,935 --> 00:42:25,900
<i>and welcome.

